description:
The general salary range for this position is $77,000- $92,000 Salary offers will be commensurate with experience, qualifications, skills, training, and education.



The Humane Society of the United States (HSUS), the nation’s most effective animal advocacy organization, is seeking a Systems Engineer for the Technology and Information Solutions department. The Systems Engineer plays a pivotal role in the IT Infrastructure team, overseeing the deployment of hardware and software solutions in a large enterprise setting. This position involves providing technical leadership, evaluating software and hardware technologies, and offering recommendations and integration policies. Responsibilities encompass designing, setting standards, and implementing approaches for the company's systems, network, and infrastructure.



**You will be responsible for:**  

* Collaborating with fellow engineers and IT leadership on enterprise systems, network design, and architecture;
* Managing Microsoft Azure Active Directory and Microsoft 365 applications in conjunction with on-premises Windows Active Directory, ensuring a cohesive and secure environment;
* Working closely with the Director of Infrastructure and fellow engineers to shape and execute our infrastructure strategy;
* Acting as the global administrator and subject matter expert for all infrastructure related matters, ensuring seamless operation and alignment with organizational objectives;
* Providing support, monitoring, tests, and troubleshooting hardware and software issues related to the LAN. Recommending and scheduling necessary repairs;
* Managing the company's Windows and MAC based systems and associated infrastructure, including cloud services like Azure and AWS;
* Establishing and maintaining technical infrastructure and architecture standards to ensure that systems are scalable, reliable, secure, cost-effective, and maintainable; contributing to the development of the technology roadmap for the company;
* Performing root cause analysis of issues and providing recommendations to improve efficiencies and resolve problems. Assisting with system outages and on-call rotation as required;
* Providing support for all Service Desk tickets that are generated and assuming ownership and accountability for tickets assigned to the engineer. Including adequate follow-up and superior customer service;
* Participating in the evaluation, selection, development, and integration of new network systems and applications. Developing, implementing, and monitoring network security procedures to safeguard systems from physical harm, viruses, unauthorized users, and damage to data;
* Assisting with the creation and implementation of security standards, policies, and procedures. Reporting network operational status by gathering prioritizing information; and managing projects;
* Participating in the evaluation, selection, development, and integration of new network systems and applications. Developing, implementing, and monitoring network security procedures to safeguard systems from physical harm, viruses, unauthorized users, and damage to data. Serving as a member of the Incident Response Team (IRT) as needed;
* Performs other duties or responsibilities, as assigned.


**Qualifications and Requirements:**  

* Bachelor’s or associate degree (engineering or information systems-related field), or equivalent work experience;
* Possess a minimum of 2 years of substantial experience in Microsoft 365 support, administration, and implementation. Additionally, demonstrate a strong grasp of networking protocols and management principles;
* Experience with CRM systems a plus;
* Knowledge of local area network concepts and fundamentals;
* Knowledge of GPO, Microsoft PowerShell, and Windows domain;
* Troubleshooting skills of Servers/PC’s/laptops/printers/etc.;
* Strong knowledge of Microsoft Suite (Word, PowerPoint, Excel, Outlook);
* Comfortable in a fast-paced environment with frequent deadlines; high energy, self-motivated and proactive;
* Ability to multitask and be flexible regarding workload and assignments;
* Ability to exercise sound judgment;
* Strong written and verbal communication skills;
* Attention to detail and commitment to excellence demonstrated by the delivery of quality and timely outcomes;
* Ability to work both independently and as an effective team member in a team environment;
* Strong interest in animal protection issues preferred.


This position is in the DC Metro Area- Remote Eligible

When applying please submit your resume and cover letter as one document.



Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, age national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability, marital or parental status or protected veteran status. EOE
